{"id":2396,"date":"2013-03-27T06:11:37","date_gmt":"2013-03-27T11:11:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/in_brief_hornall_anderson_monograph.php"},"modified":"2013-03-27T06:11:37","modified_gmt":"2013-03-27T11:11:37","slug":"in_brief_hornall_anderson_monograph","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/in_brief_hornall_anderson_monograph.php","title":{"rendered":"In Brief: Hornall Anderson Monograph"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/inbrief_happy_accidents.jpg\" alt=\"2012 Brand New Awards, Winners\" \/><\/p>\n<p>It&#8217;s not everyday that a brand consultancy publishes a 482-page book, but also not every brand consultancy has been around for 30 years. <em>Happy Accidents<\/em>, published by Graphis (although not available for purchase at their site or Amazon) chronicles &#8220;Three Decades of Design and Discovery&#8221; of the Seattle-based firm <a href=\"http:\/\/www.hornallanderson.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Hornall Anderson<\/a>. Although there is emphasis on newer work, the book does include some great 1990s work &mdash; some of which was eye-opening for me at the time &mdash; including the Jamba Juice identity, Smith packaging (not a single annual then didn&#8217;t include this one), and the Seattle Supersonics identity. The book itself is a great piece of work, with exposed binding, multiple ribbon bookmarks, and a USB drive integrated into the cover. I&#8217;ll try to track down a way of ordering the book and update the post. A few more pictures of the book are available <a href=\"http:\/\/www.hornallanderson.com\/blog\/celebrating-thirty-years\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"red\">Update:<\/span> The book will be available on <a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphis.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Graphis<\/a> in a few weeks and will retail for $160. In the meantime, you may e-mail <a href=\"mailto:&#117;&#115;&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#104;&#111;&#114;&#110;&#097;&#108;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#117;&#115;&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#104;&#111;&#114;&#110;&#097;&#108;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;<\/a> if you are interested in obtaining a copy.<\/strong><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[26],"tags":[462,851],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2396"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2396"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2396\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2396"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2396"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?